A brief memorial wherein the present case of the antient leasees, the inward pawn sub-tenants, and the outward pawn present tenants, of the Royal exchange [is] ... stated. : As also some animadversions ... relating to the ... revenue of the said place ... / By an unfeigned welwisher to the flourishing estate of the city of London ... T. P. (Theophilus Philalethes)
[2], [49] p.
[s.n.], London, : Printed Anno Dom. 1674.
